     1	// RWByteAddressBuffer.Load<IFoo> and .Store<IFoo> for existential types.
     2	//
     3	// ByteAddressBuffer provides raw byte-level access, and Load<T>/Store<T>
     4	// with an interface type T should pack/unpack the existential tuple
     5	// (RTTI + WitnessTableID + AnyValue) at the given byte offset.
     6	//
     7	// BUG (#10376): This currently crashes with ICE 99999 on SPIRV
     8	// ("Unhandled local inst in spirv-emit: lookupWitness") and HLSL
     9	// ("unexpected IR opcode during code emit"). On CPU the shader runs
    10	// but produces empty output. Disabled until the emit stage handles
    11	// existential types in ByteAddressBuffer Load/Store.
